Right now, I want to write something, but I don't know where to start.

The opening line is a cliche. Perhaps the essence of writing is a return, a return to the greatness of our predecessors. This is another mountain that makes me desperate today: The pen of my predecessors.

Earlier today, when I first tried to write down my emotions, a line from North Island came to mind:

I can only choose the sky

Never kneel on the ground

To make the executioners look big

To ward off the winds of freedom

I suddenly realized that North Island had written down all my first feelings, and my hand was off the keyboard.

Then more anger, emotion, sound, and yelling flooded my screen. It was like a ferocious wave, about to tip over the boat in the contrary direction of the storm. I was moved by the beauty and harmony of the thunder and the waves, and wanted to join in the resonance of nature, but found these sentences in the open space between the sea and the sky:

In the name of the Sun

The dark openly preys

Silence is still the story of the East

The people painted the ancient frescoes

And live forever in silence

Die In silence

Here:

I have to admit,

In the cold white light of death

I. . . Shuddered

Who wants to be a meteorite

Or the cold statues of the victims

Watching the fire of youth go on

In someone else's hands

Even if the dove lands on your shoulder

Can't feel the heat or the breath

They groom their feathers

And then they fly away

All my life

I've lied many times

And yet he has faithfully observed

A childhood promise

So that with the heart of the child

Incompatible worlds

And never forgave me

THESE -- Foshan!

ME, standing here

To replace the one who was killed

There's no other choice

Where I fell

There will be another man on his feet (these four paragraphs are from the end or the beginning, to Yu Luoke) 

Spicy, precise, vicious! My emotions and thoughts were in a state of chaos, but more than 40 years ago in North Island, all of these were written in the most impactful lines ever!

Does the world need more writers? I was in self-doubt. I ask myself that when the voices of confrontation come to an end, it terrifies North Island itself (in an interview, North Island talks about resistance to early works such as the answer) , should we, those of us who do not have the ability to write, write down our general feeling of sameness and the Paleness of language?

I asked my friend. I expressed this breakdown to her.

Writing is about empathy, she says. Transcending everyone just resonates with the vast majority.

Right.

When all men roar, that's when all men resonate.

The resonance of the universe, beyond the limits of human endurance, will stop everything in the honest, born, growing, sucking, laughing, crying, angry, fed by the waters of the Yellow River and the Yangtze River! As crushing all the reactionaries before the people in the power of shouting!

The North Island and the munks were the spokesmen for the youth in the 1980s, so the new wave of poetry spread all over China in the 1980s. But who would have thought, when the needle dial 2020, this spokesman, or let them carry; we face, is still the sky that bloody shield!

One of the deeper reasons for the popularity of new poetry is that North Island and others have set up a new personality cult to counter the official one. In essence, it is still a continuation of the Oriental story -- that the face of the sun is always changing, always the same as the only sun. We always need someone to follow, to believe. What's more, the language style that North Island and others used to fight the official language style was revolutionary -- a style that, until now, had seemed to be a throwback to the 19th century

I do not Florida Florida believing! (answer)

The revolution overthrows the revolution, this seems to be the Oriental Sad Samsara.

But these reflections should not be an excuse to stop us from seeking change.

We don't believe because we want to believe, but we can't find anything to believe.

Individual, freedom, dignity, humanity, morality, Justice —— Harvard University

What do we have and what don't we have? We stand here, on this thousand-year-old land, on the ancient and modern things that "the princes and princes would rather have the guts" and be laughed at, on the Red Dust that has swept everything away, we want to believe.

We do not believe in western discourse hegemony, and we understand the inherent contradictions of the political system. There is no government in this world that is not attacked. There is no perfect system.

All we want is to have the full dignity of a citizen.

I don't even want to use "we" anymore. I" doesn't stand for "we. " I don't speak for anyone.

I just want to be normal.

An ordinary man who longs to spend every evening in the eyes of his lover. I want love, I want trust, I want to see everyone calm and happy.

When the ordinary becomes a kind of extravagant hope, the change also should have occurred.

Write together, shout together, sing together, feel like! Let the voice of the people, become the most beautiful voice on this land; let the Voice of the people, become the Voice of History; let the Voice of the people, become the most powerful voice of the Chinese nation standing in the forest of the world!
